messages.content: @urish - Awesome work.

Great stuff  @urish 🙂 For fun I ran it on one of my old designs, and it worked: https://github.com/algofoogle/tt-gf180-toy/actions/runs/17800061560 -- I was surprised that the flow seems to define `USE_POWER_PINS` (and since my code was originally written to support Caravel, it's sensitive to those defines and gives a linter warning, though safe to ignore I guess).

I was thinking about using Magic's `plot` to render GDS instead of the existing renderer used by the TT actions. Maybe it will look better for IHP and GF's standard cells -- I will give it a try soon.

The verilog project template is ready!

https://github.com/TinyTapeout/ttgf-verilog-template/

One caveat: the "precheck" part will fail, and that's expected. We'll fix it over the next week or two.

messages.content: @urish - Should I promote that to people yet?

Everyone should be able to use the template as-is right now, but we're thinking to only open submission for people who submitted to a Tiny Tapeout shuttle in the past (our past experience shows that this is a good way to get higher quality submissions)
@urish - BTW Have you ever tested what happens if someone shorts VDD to GND together aggressively?
@urish - The power gating should stop it from causing any problem.
Yes, it should stop it.
But the current shuttle won't be power gated
I did one past TT, kinda have been digging around Discord looking for ideas to work on for the next run. Is there anything I can try to do with this that would be helpful?
Started a thread.
@Tim 'mithro' Ansell The power gate stops it as long as you don't enable that particular design 😅   If you do enable it, you will get potentially damaging high currents.
But have you actually tested such a thing?
No.

We had one design that had a short but it was through `li` in sky130 so it ended up drawing way more than expected and more than we recommend, but it was only ~ 15 mA which is still very much in the "chip will survive" zone.

I had a power gate test design that was meant to test high current usage in TT07 but I made a mistake in the layout so it wasn't able to generate very high current. There is a fixed version in TT08 but given I just got the chips yesterday, I'll wait a bit before trying to burn those 😅
We do have a way to mark dangerous projects post silicon, so users get warned before enabling them through the commander app
Will you be taking custom GDS on this run, or just digital LibreLane generated stuff?
Only LibreLane stuff. Without power gating it's a bit risky to accept random GDS 😅
If you manually add a power gate yourself we can consider including it
Or if might just wait for the next shuttle
Yeah makes sense, I figured that would be the case. I think I will try an assortment of digital and analog/mixed stuff in GF180 and see whichever shuttles I can get onto, whenever 🙂
BTW It's GF180MCU not GF180 🙂 -- Going to keep saying that because if successful we'll end up with multiple GF180 technologies.
Is there a way to reference / link / connect the https://discord.com/channels/1009193568256135208/1422290927816540402 channel from here?
A link (as you posted) is the way I know
You can pin the message to make it easier for others to find

This is what people see when they can’t access that channel. I think a bot is the way to go, and people I know tend to use Fletcher to teleport messages between channels and servers. I haven’t managed that particular bot myself before, though.
